      <div id="mainContent" class="main column clearfix"> 
       <h1>Mandatory&nbsp;Training&nbsp;</h1> 
       <p>The Commonwealth of Virginia requires that all full-time and part-time employees complete certain training.&nbsp; The required courses are:</p> 
       <ul class="checklist"> 
        <li><a title="Terrorism Awareness Training" href="/uploadedFiles/Administration/Finance_Administration_Support/Human_Resources/Preventing Workplace Violence (2016).pdf">Terrorism and Security Awareness</a> including <a title="Run, Hide, and Fight" href="http://www4.vmi.edu/videos/Run-Hide-Fight.html" target="_blank">Run, Hide, and Fight</a> &nbsp;</li> 
        <li><a title="Preventing Workplace Violence" href="/uploadedFiles/Administration/Finance_Administration_Support/Human_Resources/Preventing Workplace Violence (final).pdf" target="_blank">Preventing Workplace Violence</a></li> 
       </ul> 
       <h1>On-Site Training Opportunities</h1> 
       <p>Training topics are&nbsp;developed and prioritized based on interviews with supervisors,&nbsp;a training survey administered to all employees and focus groups of employees with similar job responsibilities. The focus is currently&nbsp;policy and procedure. The program will&nbsp;expand as needs and interests&nbsp;change. Some topics will be 'piloted' before being open to all of post. If you would like to participate in a pilot group, please let us know.</p> 
       <p>Recent Topics:</p> 
       <ul class="checklist"> 
        <li>Evaluations:&nbsp;Making the Required Useful</li> 
        <li>Hire in Haste, Regret in Leisure</li> 
        <li>Planning Successful Events at VMI</li> 
        <li>Retirement Topics from VRS &amp; TIAA-CREF</li> 
        <li>Nip It in the Bud: Progressive Discipline</li> 
        <li><a title="Alcohol and Other Drug Education" href="/uploadedFiles/Administration/Finance_Administration_Support/Human_Resources/AOD training (yellow) 2015-Final.pdf" target="_blank">Alcohol and Other Drug Education Training</a></li> 
        <li>Compensation Overview</li> 
        <li><a title="ADA Training 1" href="/uploadedFiles/Administration/Finance_Administration_Support/Human_Resources/ADA Training for Supervisors (v4).ppsx">Americans with Disabilities Act Training</a></li> 
       </ul> 
       <p>Contact us at 540-464-7322 or&nbsp;<a href="mailto:sporerb@vmi.edu">sporerb@vmi.edu</a> with suggestions for training topics, inclusion in a focus or pilot group, department specific training, or if you'd like to present a topic yourself. </p> 
       <h1>Off-Site Training</h1> 
       <p><a href="http://www.dhrm.virginia.gov/training/courses/descriptions.html" target="_blank"><strong>Department of Human Resource Management</strong></a><br> Links to the current schedule of classroom offerings from DHRM.<br><br><strong><a title="Commonwealth of Virginia Knowledge Center (Covkc)" href="https://covkc.virginia.gov/Kview/CustomCodeBehind/Customization/Login/COV_Login.aspx " target="_blank">Commonwealth of Virginia Knowledge Center (Covkc)</a></strong><br> Links to current online course offerings from DHRM.&nbsp; You will need to&nbsp;register with this site (<a title="detailed registration instructions" href="http://covkc.agencies.virginia.gov/core/Register.pdf " target="_blank">detailed registration instructions</a>).&nbsp; Once you are registered, you have access to&nbsp;online courses as well as the schedule for courses offered around the state.</p> 
       <p>Online courses of interest to all state employees are:</p> 
       <ul class="checklist"> 
        <li>Understanding &amp; Using the Grievance Procedure</li> 
        <li>Preventing Workplace Violence</li> 
        <li>Communication Topics</li> 
        <li>22 'Management Virginia' Topics</li> 
        <li>OSHA and Other Safety Topics</li> 
        <li>Leadership Topics </li> 
       </ul> 
       <p><strong><a title="Virginia Retirement System Education" href="http://www.varetire.org/members/education/index.asp" target="_blank">Virginia Retirement System Education</a></strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br> VRS provides Retirement Education Seminars (RES) &amp; Group Counseling Services (GCS) at local community colleges (<a title="schedule" href="http://www.varetire.org/members/education/schedule.asp?sect=1&amp;topic=1" target="_blank">schedule</a>). Please note that employees may attend these seminars without using leave time, so long as the&nbsp;absence&nbsp;is pre-approved.</p> 
       <p>VRS also provides additional information about retirement planning <a title="Additional Information about retirement planning" href="http://www.varetire.org/Members/Index.asp" target="_blank">here</a>.</p> 
       <p><strong>Local Opportunities<br></strong>Local businesses offer programs, many of them free, in their area of expertise. Here are some links to listings of these events.</p> 
       <ul class="checklist"> 
        <li><a title="The News Gazette" href="http://www.thenews-gazette.com/calendar/" target="_blank">The News Gazette</a></li> 
